  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mental Health &amp; the Criminal Justice System</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Amid the widespread defunding of community mental healthcare programs across the country, the Cook County Jail in Chicago has become a default treatment center for people living with mental illness. Our project exposes the challenges and injustices of treating mental health issues through the criminal justice system: A system that is punitive by design.  We advocate for preventative solutions in community mental healthcare through our feature film, Any Given Day,  and its outreach campaign.</narrative>
  </description>
